               <death when="0578" syriaca-computed-start="0578-01-01" source="#bibl69-1">0578</death>
               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bibl69-1">La litterature sur lui est abondante : BHO, 392- 93 ; PO, XVIII et XIX ; Barsaum, Lu'lu '2 , 325-26; BSO, I, 1017-18 (J.M. Fiey). D. Bundy, dans Le Museon 91 (1978), 45- 86. Sur Je rapt de son corps, de Qasiun a Psilta, en 622, cf. M.A. Kugener dans ROC 7 (1902) , 196-217.</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">Jacob Baradaeus was a monk who born near Psilta.  The Syrian Orthodox or Jacobite church is named for him.  He ordained a separate hierarchy of Anti-Chalcedonian clergy.  He also negotiated with the empress Theodora and Harith, the Ghassanid client king.  He was ordained by Theodosius of Alexandria and travelled extensively to revive the Anti-Chalcedonian clergy.   </note>
